<DataType xmlns="http://www.gip.com/xyna/xdev/xfractmod" Version="1.8" TypeName="ExampleXynaDatatype" TypePath="xyna.example" Label="Example Xyna Datatype" IsAbstract="false">
  <Meta>
    <IsServiceGroupOnly>false</IsServiceGroupOnly>
    <Documentation>This is the documentation of a Xyna datatype.

A datatype has a TypePath corresponding to its Java package name and a TypeName which is the CamelCase Java class name.

It can contain Java primitive types (except float and Float), complex Xyna datatypes and lists of these.</Documentation>
  </Meta>
